ody, femininity, surface, appearance). Addressing a broad range of subjects, from sexuality, clothes, and cell phones to hip-hop culture, bodybuilding, and imperialism, the contributors to Etiquette challenge these traditional values—not in order to favor etiquette over ethics, but to explore the various ways in which practice subtends theory, in which manners are morals, and in which ethics, the practice of living a good life, has always depended upon the graceful relations for which etiquette provides the armature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEtiquette. 0aManners and customs. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Essays.2bisacsh1 aBarnes, Hazel E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Alison Leigh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChanter, Tina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColberg, Michael D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodman, Robin Truth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamann, Trent H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoeller, Hildegard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHooks, Bell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Don Hanlon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Lynne d, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrell, David Farrell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacDonald, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacKendrick, Karmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPappas, Nickolas, econtributor.4ctb4https: